<TITLE> Turk watchdog bans broadcasts on soldier deaths </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 ANKARA, Oct 23 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Turkey's broadcasting watchdog said on Tuesday it had banned all broadcasts inside the country concerning the deaths of at least 12 Turkish soldiers at Kurdish rebel hands. The RTUK authority, acting on a government request, said broadcasting news about the deaths "hurts the psychology of society and public order and creates an image of the security forces as weak". Turkish media have extensively covered the deaths of the soldiers on Sunday in clashes with Kurdish rebels near the Iraqi border. Many Turkish towns and cities have staged anti-rebel protests in the past few days and the government has urged restraint. The military clashes are continui
